SIMPLE: ejaculation
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ejaculation
<hw>E*jac`u*la"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>⟦eacute⟧jaculation</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of
throwing or darting out with a sudden force and rapid flight.</def>
<mark>[Archaic or Technical]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧An <xex>ejaculation</xex> or
irradiation of the eye.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The uttering of a short, sudden exclamation or
prayer, or the exclamation or prayer uttered.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In your dressing, let there be <qex>jaculations</qex> fitted to
the several actions of dressing.</q> <rj><qau>Jer.
Taylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>The act of ejecting or
suddenly throwing, as a fluid from a duct.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ejaculator</ent>⟦br⟧
